The defendant Jason E. King was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:30 AM Defendant Jason E. King appeared by video, in custody of Sauk County Jail .  Attorney Carly June Sebion appeared by video for Jason E. King.  Attorney Jeri Marsolek in court for State of Wisconsin.  State is in compliance with victim rights.  Defendant agrees to continue remotely. Enters plea of No Contest to count 1. 
Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  He understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. He understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer (1) contrary to 946.41(1); Habitual Criminality contrary to 939.62(1)(a). Defendant did not exercise his right to allocution. 

Joint recommendation for 1 year probation with conditions of costs, DNA (on file), any treatment deem appropriate by agent, AODA conditions.
No jail credit.  Attorney Sebion states he has 7 days of jail credit. 

Court adopts joint recommendation orders sentence withheld, 1 year probation, costs, AODA conditions and follow through, risk and needs assessment. DNA.  7 days credit if revoked.
